content:
Use Chat Session reports to consolidate data about agents' activities while they chat with customers. This report type defines the set of records and fields available to a report based on relationships between a primary object and its related objects.

Reports display only records that meet the criteria defined in the report type. You can create a custom report type for Chat sessions to aggregate data about your agents' activity while they support customers.

Customize Chat session reports to include columns of information such as:

* Agent: Full Name
* Assistance Flags Lowered (Agent)
* Assistance Flags Lowered (Supervisor)
* Assistance Flags Raised
* Chat Requests Assigned
* Chat Requests Declined (Manually)
* Chat Requests Declined (Push Timeout)
* Chat Requests Engaged
* Created By: Full Name
* Created Date
* Last Modified By: Full Name
* Last Modified Date
* Chat Session ID
* Chat Session Name
* Login Time
* Logout Time
* Time Idle
* Time Spent at Capacity
* Time Spent Away
* Time Spent in Chats
* Time Spent Online

This report is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.
title: Customizing Chat Session Reports in Salesforce
